org.simulationsystems.csf.common.csfmodel.messaging.messages

Interface FrameworkMessage

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameworkMessageImpl

    public interface FrameworkMessage
    The Interface used throughout the CSF to represent the XML Document (CsfMessageExchange). This interface contains several convenience methods for accessing and populating different parts of the FrameworkMessage.
    Since:
    0.1
    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    Jorge Calderon

    • Method Detail

      • addDistributedAutonomousAgent

        org.jdom2.Document addDistributedAutonomousAgent(org.jdom2.Document csfMessageExchangeDoc,
                                               org.jdom2.Element distributedAutononomousAgentElement,
                                               boolean removeChildren)
        Adds the distributed autonomous agent to a CsfMessageExchange Document. Side effect includes detaching the distributedAutononomousAgentElement from the current Document. Generally you would no longer need to use the original Document. If you do need to still use the original Document, it is best to clone the distributed autonomous agent element prior to calling this method.
        Parameters:
        csfMessageExchangeDoc - the document to add the distributed autonomous agent element to.
        distributedAutononomousAgentElement - the distributed autonomous agent element
        removeChildren - whether to remove the distributed autonomous agents first from this Document before adding the new distributed autonomous agents.
        Returns:
        the document
